00:20:45.359 --> 00:20:50.479
right? So that is kind of an interesting question on like, who wins? Where do the resources go? Do

00:20:50.479 --> 00:20:56.959
you focus on moving people to Shiny if they are using Looker? I'd say the way I would personally

00:20:56.959 --> 00:21:03.520
think about it is, what is the quickest, on the analytic side, what would be the most efficient

00:21:03.520 --> 00:21:09.439
path for getting the business what they need? And if my analysts aren't super strong in Shiny,

00:21:09.439 --> 00:21:14.800
that probably is not, to be honest, the tool we're going to use versus my data scientists,

