too. One of the anonymous questions that came up, which was a follow-up from a previous question

00:36:13.439 --> 00:36:18.239
that I can't figure out which one it was, but it was what do you mean by incurring technical debt?

00:36:22.479 --> 00:36:28.639
So I mean I'd say at the highest level it's just having a bunch of legacy systems that very few

00:36:28.639 --> 00:36:36.479
or no users are using, but maybe still contain important pieces of the business, so that would

00:36:36.479 --> 00:36:42.800
be like the highest level version. What I'm kind of referring to specifically is, I mean there's

00:36:42.800 --> 00:36:47.919
probably like an optimal point where you want to cut off expanding the tools, like I personally would

00:36:47.919 --> 00:36:53.919
not want to run a team from like a BI perspective where people were using Tableau, Looker, Mode, Shiny,

00:36:53.919 --> 00:36:58.800
like that's a lot of tools. Do you really need that many tools to get the job done? Oh, and by the way,

00:36:58.800 --> 00:37:04.479
Shiny is the only free one on that list, right, so now we're just spending money, but I'd say more

00:37:04.479 --> 00:37:11.199
importantly from a data science perspective is R and Python seem like close-knit communities. I do

00:37:11.199 --> 00:37:15.679
think if you're intermediate to strong in one, you can at least read and connect on the other,

00:37:15.679 --> 00:37:17.679
and if not contribute from a development perspective.

00:37:22.239 --> 00:37:23.760
Oh, I think somebody might have gone off mute.

00:37:26.239 --> 00:37:30.719
So, but I think what would be challenging is like if we had somebody we hired using SaaS or like

00:37:30.719 --> 00:37:36.000
MATLAB, I would have less certainty that other people could pick up their work if that person

00:37:36.000 --> 00:37:42.479
were to leave, you know, just in general, right, if their work needed a contributor to help with it on.

00:37:43.040 --> 00:37:48.879
That to me is like maybe I guess the most important aspect of not expanding too wide on the tooling

00:37:48.879 --> 00:37:55.120
perspective is like can your work be used by others, picked up, improved on while you're here or

00:37:55.120 --> 00:37:59.919
while you're gone, right, and so I think the wider your tool swath gets, the more of a risk that becomes.

